Ten winners have emerged in the recently concluded social media campaign themed ‘Red Star Valentine Challenge’, which ran from 10- 15th started on the 10th of February as special valentine activation for its loyal clientele. The campaign engaged its online fans to answer three questions across their social media handles, after which ten lucky winners were carefully selected based on the Terms and Conditions. Victor Ukwat, Executive Director of Sales and Marketing, in a conversation with journalist, said that Valentine’s Day is all about giving and showing love to friends, family, loved ones, and even strangers. A-Z Petroleum Products Limited Gets “BBB” Rating Agropartnerships Reaffirms Commitment To Agri-Business Value… “Red Star Express is always appreciative of its customers, and we decided to provide them with the opportunity to win gifts to celebrate Valentine’s Day”, he said. Kayode Agbe,the Deputy General Manager, Red Star Express, said: “I congratulate all the lucky winners, I know that the parameters set were met, and it is our special Valentine’s day gift to you”. Red Star Express Plc is a Licensee of Federal Express (FedEx) Corporation, the world’s largest delivery solutions provider. “It has over 150 offices in Nigeria, with international offices in the Niger Republic, Burkina Faso, and the Republic of Benin. Its network spans over 1,500 communities in Nigeria and 214 countries worldwide”. Red Star Express Plc is made up of four divisions and business units specialising in areas such as Express Delivery, Logistics, Freight, Outsourcing services, Supply Chain Management, E-Commerce Facilitation, Printing and Packaging, E-Archiving, as well as Agro Trade Logistics.